WEB(1): serve web pages
.LP
.br
\l'5i'
.br
.LP
.SH
SYNOPSYS
.LP
.LP
\fC
.DS L

    usage: web [-l] [-p port] [-t port] [dir]
        -l: localhost and TLS only
        -p port: port used (8080 by default)
        -t port: TLS port (8083 by default)
    
.DE
\fR
.LP
.LP
.SH
DESCRIPTION
.LP
\fI Web\fR serves the given directory (or\fC /zx/usr/web\fR if none is
given) to the web. The default port is\fC 8080\fR unless flag\fC -p\fR
tells otherwise.
.LP
.SH
EXAMPLE
.LP
Serve the files at\fC /n/web\fR to the web using port 80.
.LP
.LP
\fC
.DS L

    ; web -p 80 /n/web
    
.DE
\fR
.LP
.LP
To keep the web safe despite using the development version of all Clive
tools and packages, this command serves the underlying OS files and does
not rely on ZX (yet).
.LP
.SH
SOURCE
.LP
.IP \(bu
\fC/zx/sys/src/clive/cmd/web\fR
.LP
